      "review_summary": "The branch adds a whitespace-normalized latest-assistant-text guard before Telegram writes a delivery-mirror transcript row and updates a dispatch test to expect no mirror append when a primary reply already exists.\n\nPR surface: Source +10, Tests -7. Total +3 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. source-reproducible but not live-reproduced in this review. The linked issue supplies live v2026.6.8 JSONL evidence, and current main has a Telegram mirror append path plus cache-ttl tail behavior matching the duplicate-row shape.",
