      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): skip mirror write when primary reply already exists (#94930)",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n\r\nFixes #94930.\r\n\r\nEvery Telegram-originated agent turn writes a duplicate `message(role=assistant)` record `B` as a child of `openclaw.cache-ttl` ~1s after the primary reply `A`. `B` becomes the active leaf; all subsequent user messages parent to `B` instead of `A`. `A` becomes an orphaned branch, causing:\r\n\r\n- Duplicate assistant messages in WebChat\r\n- Agent re-answering already-answered questions after delays (minutes to hours)\r\n- Re-answers routing back to the original Telegram channel even after the user switches to WebChat\r\n\r\n**Observed on v2026.6.8 — 100% reproducible from Telegram, not reproducible from WebChat native.**\r\n\r\n## Root cause\r\n\r\nTwo writers touch the session transcript per Telegram turn:\r\n\r\n- **A**: embedded runner (normal agent execution path — `appendAssistantMessageToSessionTranscript`)\r\n- **B**: `mirrorTelegramAssistantReplyToTranscript()` in `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.ts` — calls `appendSessionTranscriptMessage()` **directly**, bypassing the facade and its delivery-mirror dedup helpers\r\n\r\nAfter prompt+compaction, `attempt.ts` appends an `openclaw.cache-ttl` custom node which becomes the active leaf. ~1s later the mirror appends `B` parented to that node, making `B` the new active leaf instead of `A`.\r\n\r\n`appendSessionTranscriptMessageLocked` has an idempotency check via `readMessageIdempotencyKey`, but the mirror writer's constructed message has **no `idempotencyKey`** field — the check returns `undefined` and is skipped, so `B` is written unconditionally.\r\n\r\n**Note:** commit `f5eddc2b6d` patched `findLatestEquivalentAssistantMessageId` in `transcript.ts` and the WebChat rendering layer, but the Telegram mirror writer calls `appendSessionTranscriptMessage` directly — that facade path patch does not prevent the duplicate write.\r\n\r\n## Fix\r\n\r\nIn `mirrorTelegramAssistantReplyToTranscript()` (`extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.ts`), before calling `appendSessionTranscriptMessage`, read the transcript tail via `readLatestAssistantTextFromSessionTranscript` and compare its text to the mirror text. If they match, the primary runner already wrote the reply — skip the mirror write entirely.\r\n\r\nChanges:\r\n- `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.ts` — guard in `mirrorTelegramAssistantReplyToTranscript` (~15 lines net)\r\n- `extensions/telegram/src/bot-message-dispatch.test.ts` — updated tests\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n\r\n`pnpm test extensions/telegram` → **2162 passed, 0 failed**\r\n\r\n## Real behavior proof\r\n\r\n### Issue addressed\r\n\r\nTelegram-originated agent turns produce a duplicate `role=assistant` JSONL row (`model: delivery-mirror`) as a child of the `openclaw.cache-ttl` node, corrupting the session tree and causing WebChat to render each reply twice.\r\n\r\n### Environment tested\r\n\r\nPersonal OpenClaw setup, session `030bea8e-ddc0-4c95-934b-8c89fc7dd040`, v2026.6.8, macOS, Telegram bot channel → WebChat cross-channel.\r\n\r\n### Exact steps or command run after the patch\r\n\r\n1. Send a message to the OpenClaw agent via Telegram bot\r\n2. Open the same session in WebChat\r\n3. Observe that only one assistant bubble appears (no duplicate)\r\n4. Inspect session JSONL: confirm no second `role=assistant` row parented to `cache-ttl` node\r\n\r\n### Evidence after fix\r\n\r\nBefore fix — live JSONL from session `030bea8e` (reproduced prior to this patch):\r\n\r\n```\r\n14:25:09 message id=95dbc41a par=74d45537 role=assistant ← A (primary reply, embedded runner)\r\n14:25:09 custom id=bfa1edcb par=95dbc41a kind=cache-ttl ← cache-ttl inserted as active leaf\r\n14:25:10 message id=8d1b4c19 par=bfa1edcb role=assistant ← B (delivery-mirror duplicate)\r\n14:26:33 message id=c3f2a801 par=8d1b4c19 role=user ← next user msg parents to B, not A\r\n```\r\n\r\nFull evidence with tree diagrams: https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw/issues/94930#issuecomment-4752524069\r\n\r\nAfter fix — live JSONL from the same session with patch applied to the installed dist, Telegram-originated turn (message: \"测试\"), 2026-06-20T03:12 GMT+8:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncustom id=2aaf2f5f par=918f1b2d customType=openclaw.cache-ttl\r\nmessage id=3d4659ae par=2aaf2f5f role=user\r\nmessage id=816e1778 par=3d4659ae role=assistant model=claude-sonnet-4-6 ← A (primary, no B follows)\r\nmessage id=f571e312 par=816e1778 role=toolResult\r\nmessage id=debd14fc par=f571e312 role=assistant model=claude-sonnet-4-6\r\n```\r\n\r\nNo `model=delivery-mirror` row appears after the `cache-ttl` node. `mirrorTelegramAssistantReplyToTranscript` read the transcript tail, found the primary reply text matched, and returned early without writing.\r\n\r\n### Observed result\r\n\r\nNo duplicate assistant message row in the session JSONL after a Telegram-triggered turn. WebChat renders one bubble per turn. Session tree corruption eliminated.",
